quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,100,"[As for] the foremost, the first among the Emigrants and the Helpers, and those who followed them with virtue, God is content with them, and they are content with Him. And He has prepared for them Gardens with rivers running below, to abide therein forever. That is the great triumph"
  9,101,"Among the Bedouin around you there are hypocrites, and among the people of Madinah, who are headstrong in hypocrisy. Thou knowest them not; We know them and We shall punish them twice. Then they shall be relegated to a great punishment"
  9,102,"And [there are] others who admit their sins; they mixed righteous deeds with others that are evil. It may be that God will relent unto them. Truly God is Forgiving, Merciful"
  9,103,"Take thou a charitable offering from their wealth, cleansing them and purifying them thereby, and bless them. Truly thy blessings are a comfort for them. And God is Hearing, Knowing"
  9,104,"Know they not that God accepts repentance from His servants, and receives the charitable offerings, and that God is the Relenting, the Merciful"
  9,105,"Say, “Perform your deeds. God will see your deeds, as will the Messenger and the believers, and you will be brought back to the Knower of the Unseen and the seen, and He will inform you of that which you used to do.”"
  9,106,"And others are made to await the Command of God. Either He will punish them, or He will relent unto them. And God is Knowing, Wise"